<title type="html"><![CDATA[Semi-Microphone support via Powerpak?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6043&amp;p=56497#p56497"><![CDATA[
The Famicom mic is actually on controller port 1's register, and I seem to remember it's on D1 or D2, bits that are connected only to the expansion port, not the controller port. Of course, you could ROM-hack the game to get it to read player 2 select.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Feb 12, 2010 6:22 am</p><hr />
