<title type="html"><![CDATA[Semi-Microphone support via Powerpak?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6043&amp;p=56496#p56496"><![CDATA[
Hi, I was just wondering if it would be difficult or not to use the select button on NES controller 2 to act as a Famicom microphone.  I think that the Famicom microphone only registered sound in general and not different volumes, but I could be wrong.  What I mean is if you wanted to use the "microphone", you would just press select on controller 2 and it would register an input for the microphone.  That way people could get past Pol's Voice in Zelda and haggle in Kid Icarus for the FDS versions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4219">nothingnew</a> — Fri Feb 12, 2010 6:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
